2007-12-11  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Lock next player with w and Page Down. Lock
	next close with w. Fire shot with mousebutton1 or Down.

	* default.c: Option newbie is removed because of the new
	client and newbie player guides.
	
2007-12-02  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Support basically arbitrary number of mouse buttons
	(previously 5 were supported). For example, if you want to fire
	shots with key x and with mouse button 456, you write in your
	config: xpilot.keyFireShot: x mousebutton456

2007-11-30  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/guimap.c: Draw walls in dark blue and filled by default.

2007-11-29  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Remove pointerButtonX options. Instead key names for
	mouse buttons are used. E.g. instead of xpilot.pointerButton1:
	keyFireShot the configuration is done by xpilot.keyFireShot:
	mouseButton1.

2007-11-23  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/: More sane handling of maxColors < 16: when drawing,
	color indices that are >= maxColors are mapped to such that are
	< maxColors.

2007-11-01  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* default.c, x11/guimap.c: New options wallDrawMode and
	decorDrawMode, which replace filledDecor, filledWorld,
	outlineDecor, outlineWorld, showDecor, texturedDecor and
	texturedWalls.	For wallDrawMode possible values are: 1: Grid
	mode. Each wall block is painted.  2: Outline mode. Draws only
	wall outlines. Fast.  3: Filled mode. Fills walls in a single
	color.	4: Textured walls. Fills with textures if available.
	Option decorDrawMode has the same possible values, and in
	addition: 0: Don't draw.

2007-10-30  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/paintmessages.c: Option ignoreColorCodes lets user disable
	support for Q3 style color codes. Get rid of oldMessagesColor
	option. All messages are painted in messagesColor only, except
	when colored by ball messages scan or by color codes.

2007-10-12  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Default keys changed: keyTurnLeft to Left, keyTurnRight
	to Right, keyThrust to Up, keyLockNext to Next (i.e. Page Down),
	LeyLockPrev to Prior (i.e. Page Up), keyTalk to t, keyTeamTalk
	to y, keyToggleScoreList to Tab, keyYes to F1, keyNo to F2.
	Renamed function Find_option() to Get_option_by_name().
	Get value of keyYes when pressing keyExit. If none is found,
	set keyYes to F1.

2007-10-11  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/paintmessages.c: Options talkMessagesLifeTime and
	gameMessagesLifeTime which tell how long to show talk (top) and
	game (bottom) messages.  * messages.c: New way of painting talk
	messages. Instead of the old "Foo. [Bar]" format, the message
	is shown as "Bar: Foo." and "Foo. [Bar]:[2]" is painted as "Bar:
	2: Foo.".

2007-10-08  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Remove keyIdMode which toggles showing of player user
	and host. Instead of this the player can use keyToggleScoreList
	(default Tab).

2007-10-06  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* default.c: The client supports nicks of up to 79 chars long and
	sends exactly what the player specified to the server. Previously
	the client would limit the nick to 15 characters and would
	make certain other changes in the nick. For this feature to be
	useful, the server also has to support long nicks and have less
	restrictive rules about what nicks are allowed.  * x11/guimap.c:
	Use function ColorDrawString to paint many of the in-game
	text strings. Add shadows to most text on screen, painted in
	shadowColor. This is useful when using textured or filled walls.

2007-09-30  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/paintmessages.c: Implementation of multi-color
	messages. Messages are colored using Quake III Arena style color
	codes: http://wolfwiki.anime.net/index.php/Color_Codes

2007-09-26  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/widget.c: Support Q3A color codes in color options
	in xpilotrc, \get, \set, config window. This means that
	e.g. xpilot.wallColor: ^4 works.

2007-09-21  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/guimap.c: New scoreListColor option. Change default
	visibility border color to dark gray.

2007-09-21  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Default recordfile is now bloodspilot.xpr and toggle
	record button is F12.

2007-09-18  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* shipshape.c: The client internally stores ship angles in
	a float (radians). This system seems to support 69 million
	different angles between 0 and 2*pi. The purpose is to later
	extend the protocol and add support in the server for more than
	128 different ship directions. Rotations are done in real time,
	instead of using precomputed ship shapes.

2007-09-16  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/painthud.c: Left adjust names in score list. Keeps them
	farther away from the view.

2007-09-11  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/: For color options, value 0 now means black and not "don't
	draw". Color options can be set to value 'off', which means
	"don't draw".

2007-09-09  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/guimap.c: Paint enemy ships and self in life colors,
	and teammates ship in blue with names below ships in life colors.

2007-09-04  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* messages.c: Make messagesToStdout work as follows: 0: Don't.
	1: Only player messages (top messages).  2: Player messages
	and kill-/ballstats.  3: Player messages, kill-/ballstats and
	server Default is 2.

2007-09-03  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* event.c: Get rid of option keyPointerControl. Mouse control
	is enabled by clicking the ship or its vicinity with left mouse
	button. Mouse control is exited by pressing Escape.

2007-09-02  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/guimap.c: Paint hud lock and bases with life colors (by
	default yellow when one extra life is left, red on last life).

