2007-08-17  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* x11/painthud.c: Don't paint the old (xpilot.org/xpilot-ng)
	radar in the upper left corner at all.

	* all: Started merging BloodsPilot Client v1.3.7 with XPilot NG
	Client v4.7.2.	Notable features in the BloodsPilot client were
	a new way to paint the walls on the HUD Radar and a new score
	list, which removed the need for a separate 256 pixel wide area
	for radar and score list at the left side of the screen. Notable
	features in the XPilot NG client were e.g. support for polygon
	(NG) maps, and usability enhancements from Erik Andersson's
	"marahacked" client, for example base warnings.
